Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, They Love Each Other, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Friend Of The Devil, Little Red Rooster, Ramble On Rose, Let It Grow

Set 2

Finiculi Finicula-> Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Playin' In The Band-> Johnny B. Goode, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
It's MOTB, it's Awesome This sounds very fat and upfront without a doubt.  Great strong presence for an aud tape.

I could do without the guys singing along during FOTD and others, but it's all part of the FOB experience.

A dog with fleas! This show is total garbage. The band had no interest in playing Syracuse on this night and it has absolutely no redeeming feature whatsoever! It just might be the worst played show of the 80's. Just because you attended does not make it good. I was there, it sucked ass!
Jim Vita Jim Vita made great tapes. He made copies for me of some of his cassette masters on his dubbing deck, I still have them great taper peace be to your soul Jim!

Spring '82 Syracuse I've always enjoyed this show, granted I'm from Syracuse and it means something extra to me, but I come back again and again for the Playin->UJB.  Obviously everyone has a different point of view.
